      "note_no": "2647",
      "note": "For the same reason as in the last note, we have the consequences of Guidance to the individual, viz.: being saved from going astray or from falling into misery and despair. In 2:38, the consequences expressed, though they apply to the individual, are also appropriate taken collectively: \"on them shall be no fear, nor shall they grieve.\""
